== English ==
=== Etymology ===
From the [[Old French]] ''[[deignier]]'' from [[Latin]] ''[[dignari]]'' "to deem worthy" from ''[[dignus]]'' "accept graciously"

=== Intransitive Verb ===
'''deign''' (''+ infinitive'')
# to [[condescend]], [[denote]]s [[distaste]] due to [[superiority]]
#: ''he didn't even '''deign''' to give us a nod of the head, he thought us that far beneith him''

=== Transitive Verb ===
'''deign'''
# to condescend to give; to do something 
#: ''they didn't deign us our clothing before we were put outside''